JOHANNESBURG - The Hawks on Sunday said it is looking into allegations that North West Premier Supra Mahumapelo gave former president Jacob Zuma cattle bought with public funds. The gift was reportedly worth R1,5-million. A Sunday Times report alleges 24 cows and a bull were delivered to Zuma’s Nkandla home in KwaZulu-Natal back in October 2016. The herd was allegedly meant for emerging farmers. READ: Pressure mounts for North West Premier Supra Mahumapelo's exit The report says Zuma accepted the delivery himself. Mahumapelo is facing mounting calls for him to leave office amid allegations of corruption and maladministration. Violent protests erupted in his home province this week with residents demanding the premier’s head. eNCA